BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:be6e9277-d7a5-443c-9afe-6f43d31ba1dd@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T172000Z
DTEND:20260317T174000Z
SUMMARY:The Stanford Playbook: AI-Driven Operational Efficiency to Win
DESCRIPTION:Why companies without Artificial Intelligence in key processes will fail and how to prevent it. We'll see use cases that are already generating economic value from day one\; and a plan to react to the biggest technological disruption since the Industrial Revolution. It's not just a conference\; it's also a live demonstration of an AI interview for a recruitment use case\, and how it translates into economic value for companies.\n\nSpeakers: Claudio Guardado
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:da82c583-d97a-46b5-a145-82dfaf071fb6@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T172000Z
DTEND:20260317T180000Z
SUMMARY:Purposeful leadership: training that transforms realities
DESCRIPTION:The objective of this space is to explore how education is a key enabler of humanistic leadership and personal development\, and how these elements translate into social\, business and community impact\, aligned with the spirit of the Eugenio Garza Sada Award.\n\nSpeakers: Geraldina Silveyra León\, Uriel Vega Rodríguez
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:008da0e2-cbdd-4f0b-845c-01885433ef34@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T172000Z
DTEND:20260317T180000Z
SUMMARY:How an Advisory Board Guides Companies to Invest in\, Implement\, and Scale with Artificial Intelligence
DESCRIPTION:In this session\, Ibar and Marcelo (co-founders of elery) and Marco and Sandra\, the company's advisors\, will share their experience on how the guidance and support of an advisory board boosted their business development to scale with AI\n\nSpeakers: Ibar Langle\, Marcelo Cruz\, Sandra López
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5c931a2e-3b5b-45ff-98dd-44e9bb39f56c@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T172000Z
DTEND:20260317T180000Z
SUMMARY:Innovation Trends: Texas\, Silicon Valley\, and Nuevo León
DESCRIPTION:This panel will explore how leading innovation hubs—Silicon Valley\, Texas\, and Nuevo León—are shaping the future of AI\, entrepreneurship\, and cross-border investment. Speakers will discuss why Silicon Valley remains the global “North Star” for capital and networks\, the rapid rise of the Austin–Houston–Dallas corridor as a gateway for Latino founders entering the U.S. market\, and Nuevo León’s transformation from an industrial powerhouse into a growing innovation hub for AI and emerging technologies. The conversation will also highlight investment opportunities across borders\, including Silicon Valley capital in Latin America\, Texas as a bridge for startups expanding to the U.S.\, and Nuevo León’s strategic role in the nearshoring momentum under USMCA. The panel will conclude with a 2030 vision for how Monterrey\, Austin\, and San Jose could operate as an integrated innovation corridor—and key advice for founders seeking to raise capital across these regions.\n\nSpeakers: Brenda Bravo\, Jesse Martinez\, Carlos Serna Gamez
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:227f1946-1e48-4aac-8b54-dc9748f595bb@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T173000Z
DTEND:20260317T180000Z
SUMMARY:Meet & Greet Maca Rivera
DESCRIPTION:“It’s time to take the ‘gossip’ to the next level! Join us in this exclusive space with Macarena Riva\, the mind behind Chisme Corporativo. In this Meet & Greet\, we’re setting aside the PowerPoints and formalities to dive into an honest conversation about the realities of entrepreneurship\, raising capital\, and scaling businesses in Mexico.If you’re a fan of the podcast\, this is your chance to meet ‘Maca’ in person\, ask those questions that don’t fit in a LinkedIn comment\, and share your own corporate-life anecdotes.”\n\nSpeakers: Maca Riva
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ea5f836b-33ff-45cc-8c0b-83144e49cb59@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T173000Z
DTEND:20260317T190000Z
SUMMARY:Bakery Product Reformulation Workshop: Egg Substitution
DESCRIPTION:Content: Techniques and alternatives to eliminate eggs in bakery recipes while maintaining quality\, flavor\, and texture\; with a focus on allergies\, vegan options\, and cost reduction.\n\nSpeakers: Escuela de ingeniería y Ciencias  (EIC)
LOCATION:TEC | Centro de Biotecnología (3er piso) | Laboratorio de Cereales
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2b353262-8b40-4db0-8bd0-8db2212c0a17@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T174000Z
DTEND:20260317T181000Z
SUMMARY:BACK TO PRESENCE
DESCRIPTION:A bodily and sensory experience that allows you to release mental noise\, return to your body\, and remember what it feels like to simply BE AND BE PRESENT.From this state of presence and inner coherence\, clarity\, creativity\, and a more conscious\, human\, aligned\, and sustainable leadership naturally emerge.\n\nSpeakers: Gizehlle García
LOCATION:TEC | (ESPACIO DE REFLEXION)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9e01b271-73dd-4115-ae08-d7de65764e25@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T175000Z
DTEND:20260317T181000Z
SUMMARY:AI data centers in Mexico
DESCRIPTION:AI and Infrastructure\n\nSpeakers: Ciro Gonzalez
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5de08859-6fe3-4edf-93a0-1158a4201716@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T180000Z
DTEND:20260320T184000Z
SUMMARY:Influencer vs Manager: The Real Formula Behind a Successful Campaign
DESCRIPTION:In the attention economy\, the success of a campaign with content creators does not depend solely on an influencer’s reach\, but on the strategy behind it. “Influencer vs. Manager: The Real Formula Behind a Successful Campaign” explores the dynamic between creative talent and the management that turns ideas into real results for brands.Through this conversation\, we examine how collaboration between influencers\, managers\, and brands enables the creation of campaigns that are more authentic\, strategic\, and measurable. From talent negotiation and positioning to execution and impact measurement\, the talk reveals what happens behind the scenes of digital campaigns that truly connect with audiences and generate value for companies.\n\nSpeakers: Gonzalo De la Torre\, Vianney Rodriguez\, Fer Elizondo\, Diego Rule
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a2003eb3-ef9b-4d8e-a617-7f20a15cc20b@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T181000Z
DTEND:20260317T183000Z
SUMMARY:Optimizing Real Estate Project Creation with Disruptive Technology
DESCRIPTION:Conference on the impact of technology on the built environment (cities) and how technology allows for improvements in the processes of creating new real estate projects\n\nSpeakers: Ruben Frattini
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2c5838a6-9bd5-4211-8ad5-3df509156af0@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T181000Z
DTEND:20260317T185000Z
SUMMARY:Scaling AI enterprise pilots with startups
DESCRIPTION:This panel\, part of the INC Monterrey agenda\, will explore how artificial intelligence is being developed\, adopted\, and scaled from two complementary perspectives: that of a corporation (Karim Touma-DeAcero) and that of a startup.Moderated by Mauricio Muñoz\, the discussion will focus on the role AI plays within each organization\, the real challenges in its implementation\, and the collaboration opportunities that arise from building an AI innovation cluster.Based on practical experiences\, the panel will offer a balanced view of strategies\, execution\, and impact\, highlighting how the convergence between corporations and startups strengthens the artificial intelligence ecosystem.\n\nSpeakers: Alfonso de los Ríos\, Karim Touma\, Mauricio Muñoz Hernández
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6e12e3d9-bd0f-48a0-b110-c2130352cc6e@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T181000Z
DTEND:20260317T183000Z
SUMMARY:Cybersecurity for Startups: Protect to Grow
DESCRIPTION:DESCRIPTION:Startups often prioritize speed and growth\, leaving security in the background. However\, digital risks can compromise everything from customer trust to business continuity.OBJECTIVE:To provide entrepreneurs and startup leaders with a clear understanding of the most relevant cybersecurity risks in early stages\, along with practical recommendations to integrate security from the start as an enabler of growth\, trust\, and operational continuity.\n\nSpeakers: Elí Emmanuel Ruíz\, Ernesto Uriel Rey Guillen\, Alberto Isaías Barrón Loredo
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ca4dc03b-422a-43c1-a320-32bcaa992c05@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T182000Z
DTEND:20260317T184000Z
SUMMARY:Legality and public policies
DESCRIPTION:Learn about the CCE Director's perspective on legality and public policies in Mexico\n\nSpeakers: Jose Medina Mora Icaza
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2b8ff6d0-27d3-4feb-818b-596bb42bf687@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T183000Z
DTEND:20260317T190000Z
SUMMARY:Meditation practice. "Here and now: training attention"
DESCRIPTION:This 25-minute in-person meditation practice\, based on the Healthy Minds program and developed by the Tecmilenio Institute of Purpose and Integral Wellbeing\, invites you to pause the daily rhythm and train mindfulness through guided breathing exercises and awareness of the present moment.\n\nSpeakers: Ana Belém García
LOCATION:TEC |  | (ESPACIO DE REFLEXION)
END:VEVENT
