UID:084af65b-6511-46a1-be92-730b71255f06@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T184000Z
DTEND:20260317T192000Z
SUMMARY:AI and the future of work
DESCRIPTION:I talk about job trends\, what the future of work is\, and what role AI plays.\n\nSpeakers: Luis Felipe Peña Gaviria
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:f6b6c7ab-8a79-4e22-acd0-d7c8dbbcaf99@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T184500Z
DTEND:20260317T193000Z
SUMMARY:CASA EXATEC "Connecting to Transform: The Value of the EXATEC Community"
DESCRIPTION:Exclusive for EXATEC: A space to connect and strengthen the bonds of the EXATEC community.\n\nSpeakers: Zinia Padilla Rodríguez
LOCATION:TEC | CASA EXATEC | (TEC LOUNGE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0aa9f395-8ffa-4191-8ab6-081aabcaef49@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T185000Z
DTEND:20260317T191000Z
SUMMARY:Life and Entrepreneurship
DESCRIPTION:Through the lens of wellbeing science and positive psychology\, Rosalinda explores how resilience\, purpose\, and emotional management are not just 'soft skills\,' but strategic assets that determine the longevity of a founder and their team. Attendees will discover practical tools to align their business goals with their life projects\, understanding that a healthy entrepreneurial ecosystem begins with leaders who know how to integrate their wellbeing as the primary engine of their productivity and global vision.\n\nSpeakers: Rosalinda Ballesteros
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:152d815b-6e02-4bef-95a1-817e0ae3852d@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T190000Z
DTEND:20260317T193000Z
SUMMARY: incMTY 2026 Inauguration: Opening of the Latin American Innovation Ecosystem
DESCRIPTION:This official ceremony marks the formal beginning of the thirteenth edition of incMTY\, reinforcing Mexico’s commitment to technological innovation and high-impact entrepreneurship.In the presence of authorities from Tecnológico de Monterrey and the Government of Nuevo León\, as well as international delegations from Japan and the United States\, the traditional ribbon-cutting ceremony will take place. It is the moment when a vision for the future becomes a global collaboration agenda.\n\nSpeakers: Maricarmen Martínez\, Juan Pablo Murra\, Santos Guzmán López\, Betsabé Rocha\, Daniela Garza\, Kozo Honsei
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2f824573-ea46-4a09-9ebf-83d9e5d05b7a@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T190000Z
DTEND:20260317T192000Z
SUMMARY:Use and Impact of AI in Creative Media
DESCRIPTION:Talk with Practical Cases on the topic.\n\nSpeakers: David Dávila
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8a482a71-0620-45b2-b105-520007409598@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T191000Z
DTEND:20260317T214000Z
SUMMARY:Japan–Mexico Bilateral Innovation & Trade Roundtable
DESCRIPTION:Invitation-only eventTo convene a high-level dialogue among the Ambassador of Japan to Mexico\, leaders of the Japanese Chamber of Commerce and Industry of Mexico\, JICA\, JETRO\, Tecnológico de Monterrey\, and Japanese companies\, with the purpose of strengthening Japan–Mexico collaboration and exchanging perspectives on innovation\, investment\, and strategic partnerships.This roundtable will provide a space to explore opportunities for bilateral cooperation\, share insights on the evolving economic landscape\, and identify areas where institutions\, companies\, and academic partners may collaborate to foster long-term engagement between both countries.
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ef0cc61f-d5b4-4c41-8465-3e099db59e18@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T192000Z
DTEND:20260317T194000Z
SUMMARY:Beauty Boss & Rule Breaker: From motherhood to the organized chaos of a global brand.
DESCRIPTION:An inspiring talk about the growth of the Ere Perez brand until it became international\, and how she managed to balance her role as a woman\, mother and entrepreneur\, sharing lessons learned and advice to motivate new female entrepreneurs.\n\nSpeakers: Ere Pérez
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4e342f68-a643-47ec-8da8-d562efe3bc72@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T192000Z
DTEND:20260317T200000Z
SUMMARY:Invisible tensions between AI and humanity: Are we ready to face them?
DESCRIPTION:Innovation also generates tensions: between automation versus human judgment\, or efficiency versus meaning. In this space\, we will explore these frictions to make them visible\, because it is precisely where something feels uncomfortable that we must turn our attention\, explore\, and reflect upon in order to truly innovate with purpose.\n\nSpeakers: Ilana Blank\, Joss Hernandez
LOCATION:TEC | (ESPACIO DE REFLEXION)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:78c0cb37-2fc1-4613-a6b0-f87bb30f5910@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T193000Z
DTEND:20260317T195000Z
SUMMARY:Japan and Mexico: Two Ways of Building Innovation
DESCRIPTION:Fireside chat with alumni of the JICA program (“Enhancement of Startup Ecosystem”) discussing key learnings from Japan’s innovation ecosystem and how these insights can be applied in Mexico. The conversation will explore topics such as public policy\, venture capital\, and collaboration among academia\, government\, and the private sector to strengthen startups and foster global connections.\n\nSpeakers: Dulce Diaz\, Saulo Manuel Santana
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:68ef174d-b0c6-4c6b-ad85-24815bc0abde@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T194000Z
DTEND:20260317T202000Z
SUMMARY:The Industrial Revolution in the Age of Artificial Intelligence
DESCRIPTION:The next industrial revolution is being shaped at the intersection of artificial intelligence\, advanced engineering\, and digital transformation. In this keynote\, we will explore how organizations are redefining the way products are designed\, manufactured\, and operated through the convergence of AI\, Digital Twins\, and the Industrial Metaverse.As industries face increasing pressure to innovate faster and operate more efficiently\, digital technologies are enabling a new paradigm where the physical and digital worlds operate as one. By integrating artificial intelligence into engineering and manufacturing\, companies can simulate\, optimize\, and predict outcomes before anything is built.Through real examples of digital transformation\, this session will explore how the Digital Twin and the Industrial Metaverse are accelerating innovation\, enabling smarter decision-making\, and transforming how organizations bring ideas to life.\n\nSpeakers: Ricardo Rodriguez Sánchez
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3f0f673a-11c5-45a5-b098-9f46a37b9eda@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T200000Z
DTEND:20260317T204000Z
SUMMARY:Panel: Texas Innovation and Strategic Growth
DESCRIPTION:Texas has emerged as one of the most dynamic innovation hubs in the world\, where energy\, AI\, entrepreneurship\, public policy\, and global trade converge. In this high-impact session\, leaders from government\, corporate innovation\, trade advocacy\, and global venture acceleration will explore how Texas is shaping the next chapter of US–Mexico collaboration.The conversation will highlight how startups\, corporations\, and policymakers can align around strategic growth\, nearshoring\, energy transition\, and emerging technologies to strengthen the economic corridor between both regions.\n\nSpeakers: John Cowen\, Luly Castillo\, Kevin Koym
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d631e8ce-8dda-4c30-a936-3e1164c38666@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T200000Z
DTEND:20260317T204000Z
SUMMARY:World Cup legacy in Monterrey
DESCRIPTION:Panel on Monterrey's role in the 2026 FIFA World Cup\n\nSpeakers: Alejandro Hütt Valenzuela\, Maricarmen Martínez
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
