UID:ea5651c6-52a9-4f73-82dd-0db2468ad0e6@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T202000Z
DTEND:20260317T212000Z
SUMMARY:1st Llama Spanish Workshop in PotencIA MX
DESCRIPTION:Build your own AI arsenal in this free\, hands-on virtual workshop on Llama\, Meta's open language model (LLM). Learn to implement AI in your business without advanced technical knowledge\, a constant internet connection\, or monthly subscriptions. This initiative is part of the PotencIA MX Accelerator\, a Meta project in collaboration with Tecnológico de Monterrey through incMTY\, and with support from the Ministry of Economy and the Ministry of Science\, Humanities\, Technology and Innovation of the Federal Government. The workshop was created by Juan José Domínguez Ochoa\, EXATEC and founder of AK7 - Amplifik AI Inc.\n\nSpeakers: Juan José Domínguez Ochoa
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cf4bd9d2-7c5b-49fe-aa4a-78be7a68d7c8@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T202000Z
DTEND:20260317T212000Z
SUMMARY:The invisible cost of innovation: water\, data\, and conflict.
DESCRIPTION:The expansion of artificial intelligence\, data centers\, and digital infrastructure has become a new source of tension between innovation\, territory\, and social legitimacy. In various parts of the United States\, strategic projects have been canceled or halted due to community\, environmental\, and political opposition. In Mexico\, recent cases show that the innovation ecosystem still underestimates the weight of the social environment and the perception of the use of critical resources such as water.This workshop proposes a frank conversation about why technological innovation cannot advance without social management\, strategic intelligence\, and early contextual analysis. Beyond pro-innovation rhetoric\, it will address the real cost—reputational\, political\, and economic—of ignoring the territory\, and how decisions not made in a timely manner are often made later\, under pressure and conflict.Session ObjectivesAnalyze why technologically viable projects fail due to social license deficits.Highlight the role of social management\, strategic intelligence\, and ESG (Environmental\, Social\, and Governance) as enablers—not obstacles—to innovation.Connecting innovation\, digital infrastructure\, and territorial governance in contexts of water stress and social pressure.Providing criteria for entrepreneurs\, investors\, and innovation leaders to anticipate non-technical risks before they lead to project cancellations.\n\nSpeakers: Ana Teresa Carrion Chavarria
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d39673ac-4d7f-4403-96e2-1f978e737b98@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T203000Z
DTEND:20260317T211000Z
SUMMARY:Starting a Business as a Couple
DESCRIPTION:In this keynote address\, Gador Garza and Rodrigo Zubiría reveal the human and strategic side of building a business from scratch: difficult decisions\, reinventions\, and the resilience that transforms an idea into a legacy.\n\nSpeakers: Gador Garza\, Rodrigo Zubiría
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
