SUMMARY:Panel: Investing in the AI Decade: Venture trends\, cross-border capital and the LatAm opportunity
DESCRIPTION:Artificial intelligence is not just transforming startups\, it is reshaping how investors allocate capital. From early-stage angel investing to institutional venture strategies\, fund managers are redefining risk\, sector focus\, and geographic exposure.This session brings together investors actively deploying capital across the U.S. and Latin America to discuss how AI\, Sunbelt growth\, veteran-led ventures\, and emerging markets are influencing investment theses. The panel will provide founders and corporates with a realistic view of what capital is looking for in today’s market.\n\nSpeakers: Lala Elizondo\, Ryan Micheletti\, Sebastian Garzon\, Regina Zurutuza\, Otto Graff
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
