SUMMARY:SelectUSA & IncMTY’s: Mexico Pitching Session
DESCRIPTION:The Commercial Service office in Mexico is hosting at IncMTY Festival\, the pitching event for tech startups to pitch in front of a panel of judges\, including venture capitalists and other investors. Startups that are interested in expanding to or investing in the U.S. are encouraged to join.Judges: Thomas M. Hogg\, CEO incMTYLala Elizondo\, Co-Founder & Managing Principal\, Tule CapitalRyan Micheletti\, Head of Global Operations\, Founder InstituteJuliana Garaizar\, Partner\, Greenbackers Investment Capital/PortfoliaFernando Huerta\, Seals AI\n\nSpeakers: Clarissa Bonillas
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - BUSINESS INTELIGENCE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3d3f655b-0641-460e-8cbc-9d615ee6c935@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T222000Z
DTEND:20260317T225000Z
SUMMARY:Meet & Greet Simón Cohen Shark Tank México
DESCRIPTION:More than a business gathering\, this Meet & Greet is an exclusive opportunity to engage up close with Simon Cohen\, one of the most human and disruptive leaders in today’s ecosystem. Founder of Henco Global and a benchmark in conscious leadership\, Simon will share in this intimate setting the philosophy that led him to build “the happiest company in the world.”\n\nSpeakers: Simon Cohen
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0fcdf7e3-1819-4958-aadc-5bd8f28a1645@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T222000Z
DTEND:20260317T230000Z
SUMMARY:Beyond the Hype: Adoption of Artificial Intelligence and the Talent that Transforms Companies
DESCRIPTION:Artificial intelligence has generated great expectations in the business world\, but the real challenge lies in its actual adoption. In this conference\, Carlos Zenteno analyzes the difference between the hype around AI and the use cases that are currently generating an impact on productivity and data analysis.The main barriers to adoption—culture\, data\, and infrastructure—and the role of leadership in its integration are addressed. Likewise\, it reflects on the future of talent\, where critical thinking\, ethics\, and the ability to adapt become key differentiators. A practical perspective on moving toward a responsible and sustainable adoption of AI in companies.\n\nSpeakers: Carlos Zenteno
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cfde6748-92ea-42cb-ab3d-3335c87e19b3@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T223000Z
DTEND:20260317T231000Z
SUMMARY:Value algorithms: how AI is redefining business in Latin America
DESCRIPTION:Join this unmissable panel where leading experts explore how artificial intelligence is transforming business models in Latin America\, generating sustainable value and new competitive opportunities.\n\nSpeakers: Alejandro Correa\, Alexandra Solano\, Ingrid Avilés Ahued\, Jorge de Lara
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9475f9e9-2d02-40a0-b242-230f26561276@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T223000Z
DTEND:20260317T231000Z
SUMMARY:Panel: New York–Mexico: Capital\, Innovation & the New Cross-Border Economy
DESCRIPTION:New York and Mexico are redefining how capital\, corporations\, startups\, and governments collaborate in a rapidly evolving global economy. From venture capital and angel investing to Fortune 500 operational transformation and economic diplomacy\, this panel brings together leaders shaping the future of cross-border innovation.In a 40-minute high-impact conversation\, speakers will explore how AI\, private markets\, digital identity\, and global corporate ecosystems are unlocking new opportunities between both regions — and what founders\, investors\, and institutions must do to build scalable\, resilient\, and globally competitive partnerships.\n\nSpeakers: Antoine Colaço\, Carla Avila\, Jorge Paz-Soldan\, Rafael Barroso
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7051825c-365a-44ec-a9cc-218b3b0882e8@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T230000Z
DTEND:20260317T233000Z
SUMMARY:Connection
DESCRIPTION:This 25-minute in-person meditation practice\, based on the Healthy Minds program and developed by the Tecmilenio Institute of Purpose and Integral Wellbeing\, invites you to pause the daily rhythm and train mindfulness through guided breathing exercises and awareness of the present moment.\n\nSpeakers: Ariadna Romero
