BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:b7ee1cc7-0197-4743-92ae-facff4fa37fd@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T230000Z
DTEND:20260318T000000Z
SUMMARY:The Framework for Building a Global Startup in the Age of AI
DESCRIPTION:“Hard Ground” is a talk based on the real experience of building a global startup from scratch.Forget product–market fit — that concept is incomplete. Founders who truly scale master four different fits\, and confusing one for another is why most startups stall or burn through cash too early.In this session\, we’ll explore the framework that allows you to understand exactly what stage your startup is in\, which levers to pull at each moment\, and how to maintain a compact and resilient team while getting there — especially now that AI allows you to operate at a global scale with a fraction of the resources you needed just five years ago.No textbook theory. Just what actually works when you’re building in the real world.\n\nSpeakers: Leonardo Vilchis
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:48410ddb-5014-4cce-8462-b190e27c0301@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T230000Z
DTEND:20260318T000000Z
SUMMARY:Why most startups fail… and how to avoid it
DESCRIPTION:Starting a business is one of the bravest decisions a person can make.But it's also one of the most uncertain adventures.The reality is that most startups fail in their first few years. However\, it's rarely discussed clearly why this happens and what an entrepreneur should focus on from the beginning to avoid it.When someone decides to start a business\, they receive a lot of advice:"Follow your passion\," "Work hard\," "Never give up\," "Give it your all!"But almost no one explains what mistakes to avoid and what to focus on from the start.In this conference\, Juan Carlos Cante\, president of the ASEM (Mexican Association of Entrepreneurs) Council\, will present the most relevant findings from the National Entrepreneurship Snapshot\, the most comprehensive study on entrepreneurs in Mexico\, based on the analysis of thousands of entrepreneurs and their real-life experiences.Based on this data\, he will share:• The most common reasons why startups fail• The mistakes thousands of entrepreneurs make without realizing it• The factors that truly increase the chances of surviving and growingBut more importantly\, Juan Carlos will share the key principles and decisions every entrepreneur must understand from the outset to build a solid\, sustainable\, and profitable business.With over 30 years as an entrepreneur\, founder of several companies\, and more than 25 brands developed\, Juan Carlos has worked in international markets\, taught entrepreneurship at Tecnológico de Monterrey\, been a member and leader of the Entrepreneurs’ Organization (EO) globally\, and currently chairs ASEM\, Mexico’s largest entrepreneur community with over 40\,000 members.This talk combines data\, real-world experience\, and insights from the entrepreneurial ecosystem\, offering a clear perspective on what it truly means to be an entrepreneur in Mexico today.If you're starting a business or thinking about doing so\, this conference can help you avoid costly mistakes and understand which decisions can make the difference between survival and failure.You'll also learn how ASEM can support you on this entrepreneurial journey\, ensuring you're never alone on your entrepreneurial path.\n\nSpeakers: Juan Carlos Cante
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2c7290c8-8210-4847-858a-d09d3ccebb32@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260317T232000Z
DTEND:20260318T000000Z
SUMMARY:Anáhuac A-Hub and Yucatán\, emerging ecosystems for scaling technology startups
DESCRIPTION:This panel will explore how the entrepreneurial ecosystem in Yucatán\, based on its current conditions—talent\, quality of life\, connectivity\, entrepreneurial culture\, and institutional coordination—is creating an increasingly favorable environment for the creation\, growth\, and scaling of information and communication technology (ICT) startups. Through the direct experience of founders who have achieved exits\, international expansion\, accelerated growth\, and the consolidation of global teams from the region\, the key factors positioning Yucatán as an emerging hub for technological entrepreneurship in Mexico will be analyzed. This is a space to share lessons learned\, identify opportunities\, and envision the future of the digital ecosystem in southeastern Mexico.\n\nSpeakers: Alberto Ceballos\, Farique Cetina Carrillo\, Pablo Rizzi\, Fabiola Borquez\, Mayra Domínguez Zenteno
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
