SUMMARY:Economic Development through Open Innovation and High-Impact Entrepreneurship
DESCRIPTION:In this session\, the leaders of the Ministries of Economic Development from Jalisco\, Querétaro\, Mexico City (CDMX)\, Aguascalientes\, and Guanajuato discuss the strategies transforming their states into global investment hubs.Through the lens of open innovation\, the panelists will share how collaboration between government\, academia\, and industry is accelerating high-impact entrepreneurship. The discussion will address critical topics such as attracting smart capital\, leveraging nearshoring opportunities\, and building resilient ecosystems that not only generate jobs but also lead the country's technological frontier.
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
