BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1a82f61e-835c-42e6-b9ba-e7ea55276110@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T170000Z
DTEND:20260318T172000Z
SUMMARY:Book Meeting: Partner Conflicts\, Causes and Prevention
DESCRIPTION:In this book\, the author warns us about what we should do—and what we should avoid—in our daily lives so that our organizations can develop without the setbacks that often cause significant harm to society. It can serve as a guide on how business partnerships should be organized\, what we should safeguard against\, what we must avoid\, and how we should learn to be partners\, shareholders\, leaders\, or business owners. It also shows how a family or institutional company should be managed when preparing for succession.In everyday life\, it is important that our conduct be guided by conviction\, applying the rules of common sense\, morality\, and ethics accepted by our society—where one of the fundamental principles is not to do to others what we would not want done to ourselves.Solving a problem by addressing its causes rather than its effects helps prevent its recurrence and allows for a definitive resolution of the damage caused\, whether partially repaired or\, when necessary\, by acknowledging and assuming the losses incurred.The author begins by reminding us that “problems are first human and then legal\, not the other way around.” Relationships must evolve and include the foundations needed to guarantee fair and balanced treatment among their members.It is essential to rationalize\, from the moment the rules governing a partnership are established\, not only the theoretical provisions that define obligations of what should or should not be done\, but also to incorporate rights and duties whose fulfillment must be guaranteed. These rules must become guiding principles that ensure\, in practice—whether by conviction or obligation—the observance of norms and values that support a healthy business coexistence.\n\nSpeakers: Salvador Benitez
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:84c9511b-682b-4236-86cf-8aba893a228c@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T170000Z
DTEND:20260318T173000Z
SUMMARY:Navigating the Campus with VanTec
DESCRIPTION:Discover the campus through a ride in Tecnológico de Monterrey’s autonomous vehicle.Maximum capacity per ride: 6 peopleRoute: From the Campus Library to the final stop at Expedition FEMSA. 🚗
