DTSTART:20260318T172000Z
DTEND:20260318T182000Z
SUMMARY:Roadmapping: The Vision from the Future
DESCRIPTION:In the fast-paced tech world\, the urgent often takes priority over the important. How can you create product strategies that drive long-term impact? In this session\, you’ll discover how to transform complex ideas into an actionable and innovative framework. Learn how to align every team effort with business goals and user needs. Turn your vision into a concrete plan you can execute today.\n\nSpeakers: Luisa Arévalo
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cb5fe8b7-9a98-474d-98a1-0dd3823fc5c6@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T172000Z
DTEND:20260318T182000Z
SUMMARY:Japan Panel – Invited: Economic and Innovation Partnership between Japan and Mexico
DESCRIPTION:Japanese corporations\, manufacturers\, and other organizations will come together to present practical cases of innovation\, technological development\, and collaborative efforts at both the national and international levels. They will share their expectations for startups\, key considerations for collaborating with Japanese companies\, and the types of government support available\, including real-world case studies.This session represents a valuable opportunity for startups and university representatives to gain insights into collaborating with Japanese companies and expanding internationally.\n\nSpeakers: Chiaki Kobayashi\, Ryuta Fukasawa\, Satoshi Takehara\, David Campos\, Alejandro Carmona
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
