BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3e6c16a7-1bf0-4d6b-b76e-8d5ae8d21d0a@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T173000Z
DTEND:20260318T190000Z
SUMMARY:Bakery Product Reformulation Workshop: Egg Substitution
DESCRIPTION:Content: Techniques and alternatives to eliminate eggs in bakery recipes while maintaining quality\, flavor\, and texture\; with a focus on allergies\, vegan options\, and cost reduction.\n\nSpeakers: Escuela de ingeniería y Ciencias  (EIC)
LOCATION:TEC | Centro de Biotecnología (3er piso) | Laboratorio de Cereales
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2e7f199a-0ce1-476d-9834-283a9aa9be88@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T174000Z
DTEND:20260318T180000Z
SUMMARY:Life Is a Sandcastle
DESCRIPTION:Why would you invest time\, energy\, and love in creating something today—whether it's a sandcastle or your life—knowing it could disappear tomorrow?This talk will answer that question and present a simple yet profound philosophy for seeing and understanding the life you live more clearly.The intention is to make you think\, to question everything\, especially the things that make up your daily life and your comfort zone\; those things that\, too often\, don't receive enough attention or appreciation.Imagining life as a sandcastle will help you pause\, redefine your approach\, and distinguish the good and beneficial things from those that aren't. It will also give you the opportunity to open yourself to new experiences\, develop your creativity\, and even change your mind.\n\nSpeakers: Tero Moliis
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:acd1e5d6-8e27-442c-9900-fa393510fa47@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T175000Z
DTEND:20260318T183000Z
SUMMARY:MTY Digital: Government as an Engine for Innovation and Entrepreneurship
DESCRIPTION:This talk explores how local governments can become enablers of the entrepreneurial ecosystem through regulatory simplification\, the digitalization of procedures\, and the creation of institutional environments that facilitate innovation. Based on the Monterrey experience\, the session will analyze the new role of municipal government as a platform that connects talent\, investment\, and technology to drive economic growth and the development of new businesses.\n\nSpeakers: Julio Hajime Toy Ovando\, Manuel Gerardo Flores Romero\, Ximena Tamariz García\, Héctor Tijerina Morales
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3fea16f2-eed2-4a32-bb75-fba2f0db1fd1@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T180000Z
DTEND:20260318T182000Z
SUMMARY:Experimental Identity: Own the Destination in the AI Era
DESCRIPTION:AI master every “how.” The last edge belongs to those who ruthlessly own the “where.” From British Cycling’s 1% marginal gains to Kaizen standards and escaping out-of-the-loop drift\, this keynote reveals how turning experimentation into identity compounds into real power in 2026. Stop drifting as passenger. Become the architect.\n\nSpeakers: Josue González Hernández
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8463519c-5487-4b47-b9ab-87b63300b06b@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T182000Z
DTEND:20260318T184000Z
SUMMARY:Book presentation: Awakening of Colors
DESCRIPTION:Mexican illustrator Alex Carrillo will present his new book\, Awakening of Colors\, a story set in a world where creativity has completely disappeared and a group of young people come together to awaken it.The book is published by Penguin Random House.\n\nSpeakers: Alex Carrillo
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:81bef1cf-8240-4d37-91e9-66fcd46a4ae2@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T183000Z
DTEND:20260318T190000Z
SUMMARY:Insight
DESCRIPTION:Here and Now: Training AttentionA 25-minute in-person practice\, based on the Healthy Minds program and developed by the Tecmilenio Institute of Purpose and Integral Wellbeing\, that invites you to pause the daily rhythm and train mindfulness through guided breathing exercises and awareness of the present moment.\n\nSpeakers: Rosalinda Ballesteros
LOCATION:TEC | (ESPACIO DE REFLEXION)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:98b90b02-15d9-4702-875f-fec5057c4a0a@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T183000Z
DTEND:20260318T185000Z
SUMMARY:The Innovation Bridge: How Mexico\, the U.S. and LATAM Can Build the Next Healthtech Ecosystem
DESCRIPTION:How do we transform scientific talent into real solutions for millions of people?Latin America and the United States share major health challenges—from chronic diseases to aging populations—yet innovation ecosystems still operate in isolation. This conversation brings together leaders from the Inter-American Development Bank and Tecnológico de Monterrey to explore how cross-border collaboration can unlock a new generation of science-based startups.The panel will discuss how universities\, investors\, governments\, and entrepreneurs can build a binational innovation pipeline that accelerates deep-tech ventures\, validates them in real healthcare systems\, and scales solutions across the Americas.\n\nSpeakers: Josue Delgado\, Ulrick Noel\, Cesar Buenadicha
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5dea1273-8caf-442a-865b-76b60c2d6d41@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T183000Z
DTEND:20260318T190000Z
SUMMARY:Navigating the Campus with VanTec
DESCRIPTION:Discover the campus through a ride in Tecnológico de Monterrey’s autonomous vehicle.Maximum capacity per ride: 6 peopleRoute: From the Campus Library to the final stop at Expedition FEMSA. 🚗
