UID:c4b55e98-5d06-43d9-806a-5fa4372668a8@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T184000Z
DTEND:20260318T190000Z
SUMMARY:AI and the Art of Being Human
DESCRIPTION:I will present a mindset and series of practices tools that allow every individual to develop a roadmap to thrive in the age of AI based on my book\, “AI and the Art of Being Human.”\n\nSpeakers: Jeffrey Abbott
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION - AUDITORIO EXPEDITION)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5e58738a-dc32-44da-a670-ce601a5f4e47@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T184000Z
DTEND:20260318T190000Z
SUMMARY:The marketing of the future is human: How to differentiate yourself when AI makes everything "generic"?
DESCRIPTION:In an environment where artificial intelligence has democratized content production and accelerated campaign execution\, the real challenge is no longer "doing more marketing\," but rather being more relevant. This keynote proposes a central idea: when everything can be automated\, what's scarce is the human touch applied to brand design\, experience\, and relationships.Over 20 minutes\, Ronan Massez presents a practical framework for leaders and entrepreneurs to use AI as an accelerator without falling into homogenization: what to automate\, what to never delegate (empathy\, judgment\, and consistency)\, and how to build differentiation based on trust\, emotion\, and consistent experience. The result: a clear guide to moving from data-driven to human-driven marketing\, capable of generating sustainable growth and reputation in the age of AI.\n\nSpeakers: Ronan Massez
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9e5ff975-8569-4773-833b-10998a132c72@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T184000Z
DTEND:20260318T194000Z
SUMMARY:Workshop | The new era of connection: AI for the real world — TELCEL.
DESCRIPTION:What happens when aesthetic sophistication is taken to an unprecedented level? We create devices that redefine what a smartphone can do—designed to solve the real challenges of your everyday life\, even before they arise.\n\nSpeakers: Alejandro Eliasib Martínez Rubio
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:c94bb5c0-fcb4-4f27-88af-504789f280e4@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T184000Z
DTEND:20260318T194000Z
SUMMARY:From Chaos to Calm: Design Your Semester with Gemini
DESCRIPTION:Stop surviving college and start designing it. Have you ever felt like the semester is "eating you alive"? Between 50-page PDFs\, finals\, and exhaustion\, it's easy to lose control. But what if I told you that Artificial Intelligence isn't just for doing assignments\, but for giving you back your time?In this 60-minute workshop\, we'll turn Gemini and NotebookLM into your productivity empowerment squad. It's not a tech course\; it's your opportunity to discover different tools and use cases for applying AI responsibly and creatively.\n\nSpeakers: Ingrid Avilés Ahued
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5475fdd7-0b9f-4c08-85a3-aae0a77811be@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T190000Z
DTEND:20260318T192000Z
SUMMARY:Presentation of the book “AI and the Art of Being Human”
DESCRIPTION:The book “AI and the Art of Being Human” by Jeffrey Abbott (VC and founder of AI Salon) and Andrew Maynard (academic at ASU) serves as a practical guide on how to remain human while working side-by-side with AI.\n\nSpeakers: Jeffrey Abbott
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7c47783d-2e5d-49b4-a559-d2356f894265@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T190000Z
DTEND:20260318T194000Z
SUMMARY:Slow Down to Speed Up: The AI Paradox in Regulated Industries
DESCRIPTION:How can you leverage accelerated innovation in highly regulated environments where there is no room for error? In this session\, you’ll discover why security isn't a bottleneck\, but rather the engine behind AI. We will analyze strategies for scaling models with confidence\, transforming regulation into a competitive advantage\, and exploring real-world strategic execution lessons to navigate this ecosystem.\n\nSpeakers: Christian González
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:079c1540-1790-462d-852f-cecd15fb1249@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T191000Z
DTEND:20260318T195000Z
SUMMARY:Building a world-class startup: Seals AI\, Altur\, and Buildpeer
DESCRIPTION:Three founders from Monterrey and a Silicon Valley investor share the keys to creating a successful startup in 2026.\n\nSpeakers: Iván Montoya\, Luis Mario García\, Luis Olave\, Mauricio Valdes
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:52eebc26-6e34-4c6a-a8c1-d470b4ca1e48@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T191000Z
DTEND:20260318T195000Z
SUMMARY:Designed to Bloom
DESCRIPTION:In a world where artificial intelligence is accelerating the future\, Designed to Flourish reminds us that the greatest advancement remains human. By discovering and transforming our talents\, we align creativity and technology to deliver relevant\, authentic\, and essential contributions to the evolution of our society.\n\nSpeakers: Rosemary Martínez Jover
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0e086753-3482-4a61-afcb-fc32e004121c@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T194000Z
DTEND:20260318T200000Z
SUMMARY:Book meeting: The BIG 3
DESCRIPTION:In The BIG 3\, Efraín Mendicuti dismantles\, with lucidity\, humor\, and brutal honesty\, one of the great myths of the modern world: that doing more equals getting further. Drawing on his experience leading teams at global companies like Google\, Twitter\, and Pinterest\, and years of mentoring leaders\, executives\, and entrepreneurs\, the author proposes a methodology as simple as it is powerful: choosing just three top priorities to guide your energy\, your decisions\, and your life.This is not a traditional productivity book or a collection of empty formulas. It's a compass. The BIG 3 invites you to stop being trapped by pending tasks\, other people's urgent needs\, and endless lists\, and to start acting with intention\, purpose\, and clarity. Through real-life stories\, profound reflections\, and practical tools\, Mendicuti shows how focusing on what's important—at work and in your personal life—can transform results\, well-being\, and your sense of direction.With a warm\, ironic\, and deeply human tone\, the author explores themes such as purpose\, non-negotiable values\, rest as a high-performance strategy\, the difference between movement and progress\, and the power of saying “no” without guilt. The result is a method applicable to both organizations and individuals seeking more than just success: they seek coherence. The BIG 3 doesn't promise magic. It promises something better: clarity to choose\, discipline to move forward\, and awareness to build a life\, and a year\, that are truly worthwhile.\n\nSpeakers: Efraín Mendicuti
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a7044036-9483-477e-8264-eadcf6f7b578@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T200000Z
DTEND:20260319T010000Z
SUMMARY:SME Day: Graduation of the Free SME SOS Digitalization Program
DESCRIPTION:SME Day\, organized by the Center of Excellence for SME Business Development at Tecnológico de Monterrey\, is a space for learning and business connection where the national community of small and medium-sized business owners gathers at INC Monterrey.In this edition\, we will celebrate the graduation of the free SME SOS Digitalization Program\, joined by Betsabé Rocha\, Secretary of Economy of the Government of the State of Nuevo León. In addition\, we will host e-commerce workshops with the Argentine unicorn Tiendanube\, explore the impact of artificial intelligence through a workshop by Lovable\, and learn about the global opportunities available to SMEs through the international network of Small Business Development Centers (SBDC) in the United States.Note: The event will take place from 2:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. on the second floor of the Expedition Entrepreneurship Gateway building.March 1811:30 AM – 1:00 PMEXATEC SME Panel – Exclusive for EXATECTEC Lounge2:00 PM – 3:00 PMRegister\, Build\, and Improve Your Store with AI on TiendanubeMultipurpose Room\, Floor 7 – Expedition FEMSA3:00 PM – 4:00 PMDigitalize and Sell with AI by LovableEntrepreneurship Gateway\, Floor 2 – Expedition FEMSA4:00 PM – 5:00 PMGraduation of the 2nd Generation of PyME SOS Nuevo LeónEntrepreneurship Gateway\, Floor 2 – Expedition FEMSA5:00 PM – 6:00 PMSBDC: A Platform for Doing Business with the United StatesEntrepreneurship Gateway\, Floor 2 – Expedition FEMSA6:00 PM – 7:00 PMNational Gathering of the Center of Excellence for Business DevelopmentEntrepreneurship Gateway\, Floor 2 – Expedition FEMSA\n\nSpeakers: Christian Hernando Salazar Mantilla
LOCATION:Entrepreneurship Gateway | EXPEDITION FEMSA
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a2b94120-034d-4115-acce-ed2a4a14fdc1@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T200000Z
