UID:684a35cc-dd6a-41a6-9468-ecef35a9e76e@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T212000Z
DTEND:20260318T220000Z
SUMMARY:The new capitals of entrepreneurship
DESCRIPTION:Entrepreneurship no longer happens only in major global hubs. In Mexico\, a new generation of cities is demonstrating that it's possible to build ecosystems capable of generating global startups\, attracting investment\, and transforming regional economies.In this panel\, leaders in entrepreneurship\, technology\, and venture capital will share how communities are being created in Querétaro\, Hermosillo\, Puebla\, Chihuahua\, and Aguascalientes that connect talent\, capital\, universities\, and corporations to drive impactful innovation. A conversation about what it takes for more regions to become the new entrepreneurial capitals.\n\nSpeakers: Luis Almanza\, Sergio Almaguer\, Ricardo Celaya\, Fernando Vera\, Josue Delgado
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
