DTSTART:20260318T213000Z
DTEND:20260318T221000Z
SUMMARY:Why is it important for universities to foster entrepreneurship?
DESCRIPTION:The conference "Why is it important for universities to foster entrepreneurship?" addresses the key role of higher education institutions in training students capable of creating innovative solutions and generating value for society. Throughout the talk\, it analyzes how universities can promote an entrepreneurial mindset\, strengthen skills such as leadership and problem-solving\, and facilitate the connection between academic knowledge\, applied research\, and market needs. In addition\, it highlights strategies\, programs\, and examples\, such as the Monterrey Innovation District\, which demonstrate how entrepreneurship and innovation contribute to economic development\, job creation\, urban transformation\, and social innovation.\n\nSpeakers: Mario Adrian Flores
LOCATION:TEC | INSPIRE STAGE | (RECTORIA - SALA MAYOR)
