BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5c3af83b-ae6c-4d4d-953b-d3ebec96c7e1@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T220000Z
DTEND:20260319T000000Z
SUMMARY:Connecting Valley: The Challenges of Building Communities
DESCRIPTION:Building a community is not difficult. What’s difficult is making it last.In innovation ecosystems\, many of the people involved are leaders: founders\, executives\, builders—individuals used to making decisions\, holding the microphone\, and leading. The challenge is getting many ‘alphas’ to coexist\, set aside their egos\, and truly collaborate.In this roundtable\, we will discuss what is rarely said about building communities:How to create spaces where the spotlight is sharedHow to transform networking into real collaborationAnd how to ensure a community not only grows\, but enduresBecause building a community is not about volume.It’s about trust\, collaboration\, and shared purpose.
LOCATION:TEC | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - VENTURE CAFE)
END:VEVENT
