DTSTART:20260318T222000Z
DTEND:20260318T230000Z
SUMMARY:Brewing Success: Lessons from Starbucks' Early Days
DESCRIPTION:In this exclusive session\, Starbucks co-founder Zev Siegel joins Jose Manuel Aguirre for a journey back to the roots of one of the world’s most influential brands.Beyond the lattes and logos\, this conversation dives into the "strategic gossip" of the early days: from funding challenges and choosing the right name\, to the obsession with quality that defined their DNA. Zev will share critical lessons on execution and resilience learned long before the brand became a household name.\n\nSpeakers: Zev Siegl\, José Manuel  Aguirre
LOCATION:TEC | TELCEL 5G STAGE | (CENTRO DE CONGRESOS - SALA 1 Y 2)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2f7ff673-4b4d-4d8c-8b17-8c2cc2b7ffdd@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T223000Z
DTEND:20260318T225000Z
SUMMARY:Building the Bridge: How AI Infrastructure Unlocks the Japan–US–Mexico Ecosystem
DESCRIPTION:On March 16\, Mexico and the U.S. begin a high-stakes review of the T-MEC trade agreement. While the experts talk about complex rules and tariffs\, the real challenge for business owners is simpler: How do you prove your product is Made in North America without drowning in paperwork?For manufacturers in the Japan-US-Mexico corridor\, staying compliant with tax authorities like the SAT is becoming a digital-first battle. This session explores how AI is building a digital bridge that automates the proof-of-origin process. We will discuss how this AI-native verification layer doesn't just satisfy government auditors—it helps SMBs get paid faster. Join us to discover how AI is moving beyond the hype to solve the 90-day payment cycle and build a supply chain where small businesses can finally compete on a global scale.El 16 de marzo\, México y Estados Unidos inician una revisión crucial del acuerdo comercial T-MEC. Mientras los expertos hablan de reglas complejas y aranceles\, el verdadero reto para los dueños de empresas es más simple: ¿Cómo demuestras que tu producto está Hecho en Norteamérica sin ahogarte en el papeleo?Para los fabricantes en el corredor Japón-EE. UU.-México\, cumplir con las autoridades fiscales como el SAT se está convirtiendo en una batalla totalmente digital. Esta sesión explora cómo la IA está construyendo un puente digital que automatiza el proceso de certificación de origen. Analizaremos cómo esta capa de verificación nativa de IA no solo satisface a los auditores gubernamentales\, sino que ayuda a las PyMEs a cobrar más rápido. Acompáñanos para descubrir cómo la IA va más allá del entusiasmo mediático para resolver el ciclo de pago de 90 días y construir una cadena de suministro donde las pequeñas empresas finalmente puedan competir a escala global.\n\nSpeakers: Nishant Dixit
LOCATION:TEC | CREATE WORKSHOPS | (BIBLIOTECA - SALA POEMA & DIALOGO)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7bf0f2e7-d0e3-4e1b-a9a9-eca1076605b1@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T224000Z
DTEND:20260318T230000Z
SUMMARY:Unstoppable ventures: when youth and experience come together
DESCRIPTION:Does success in entrepreneurship have a birth date? The short answer is no. The real answer is that success favors the mix.In a world that tells us we must choose between the speed of youth and the security of experience\, we propose something bolder: the union of both. This is not just a talk about business\; it is the meeting point where disruptive ideas find the method to become reality.Why should you be here?If you’re young and driven: Discover how the seasoned “edge” and network of someone more experienced can save you years of costly mistakes and accelerate your path to market.If you bring experience and a proven track record: Reconnect with cutting-edge innovation and discover how your expertise is the fuel new business models need to scale with strength and stability.For everyone: You’ll learn why intergenerational teams are\, statistically\, the most resilient and profitable in today’s ecosystem.Don’t come just to listen\; come to find the missing piece of your next great project.\n\nSpeakers: Luis Garza Hoth\, Rolando Jose Porchini Cano
LOCATION:TEC | INNOVATION WORKSHOP | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - SALA POLIVALENTE)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7afc2c91-411a-4f60-9fec-4862aa52defd@incmty2026
DTSTART:20260318T224000Z
DTEND:20260318T230000Z
SUMMARY:What They Don’t Teach You at University: From Engineer to Leader of Leaders
DESCRIPTION:What separates those who accelerate their careers from those who simply follow the path? In this talk\, Ryan Poskitt shares lessons from his journey from engineer to leader of leaders in a global organization. Through personal experiences\, he explores how to define a clear career vision\, turn ideas into action\, and develop the skills companies value most — including communication\, collaboration\, and leadership. A practical and inspiring conversation for participants looking to stand out in an increasingly competitive professional environment.\n\nSpeakers: Ryan Poskitt
LOCATION:TEC | BOLD VISION | (EXPEDITION FEMSA - AUDITORIO)
END:VEVENT
